</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">EQ2 of course nothing like EQ1 in many aspects specially in those cross class abilities none the less then I was looking on class that I want to play I found Coercer and Necromancer suit me best - both heavy doters with massive debuffing abilities that allow my spells work on full regardless major difference comes that coercer in DPS might relay on charmed pet and multiple mental based nukes and able fast combat mana regenerate via powerdrain while necro bring on table undead pet and restore power in a traditional way liching and life taping. Main reason why I picked main as Enchanter fact that I hate to see that half population of Norath is summoners and enchanters are far far rare (not as rare as fighters but rare)
<br />

<br />
..
<br />

<br />
I read through most of this thread and I have to say that at level 21 I am enjoying my Coercer quite a bit and dont feel gimped at all. 
<br />
 
<br />
I have backed of on nuking considerably now when we fight hard mobs and I feel much more needed in a utility way then as a nuker. 
<br />
 
<br />
I have 5 group buffs right now and they only use 1 concentration point each so I can keep them up at all times. I also have a single target power regen called Breeze that is very nice for the healers and myself and costs no concentration. I can keep it on 2 healers and myself at all times making 6 buffs I am maintaining with no problem. 
<br />
 
<br />
I also have 2 roots, 2 stuns, 3 dots, and in a few bubbles I will have 2 mezzes. 
<br />
 
<br />
I can use consume ego to constantly keep my power going up even during fights and if the fight is going bad I can mez the boss or mob and keep him locked down while breeze FULLY recharges the healer and tank and then we finish him off with no problem.
<br />
 
<br />
I shine so well when I am in a group that when we get add ons its to the point where my tank just says "Mob Add" and I handle the rest and they never miss a beat. We have been spawned on twice in a row before deep into FG and still came out no problem. In fact the only time we ever have a death is because we take on a mob who changes aggro at the end of fight which will happen sometimes.
<br />
 
<br />
Anyone who thinks Enchanters are gimped needs to just give it till 20 and see how you feel. If you dont like buffing the group and taking control of bad situations then this isnt the class for you. We dont do much damage but we make sure the damage doesnt get dished out by the mobs we control.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
